# Job Finder App

This is a React Native app that allows users to login and view popular and featured job listings.

## Features

* Login screen with name and email input fields
* Home screen that displays the user’s name and email
* Popular and featured job listings displayed as cards
* Each job card displays the job title, company, and location

## Installation

1. Clone the repository: `git clone https://github.com/your-username/job-finder-app.git`
2. Install dependencies: `npm install` or `yarn install`
3. Start the app: `npx react-native start` or `yarn react-native start`

## Usage

1. Open the app on a simulator or physical device
2. Enter your name and email on the login screen
3. Press the “Login” button to navigate to the home screen
4. View the popular and featured job listings on the home screen

## Components

* `LoginScreen.js`: Handles user login and navigation to the home screen
* `HomeScreen.js`: Displays the user’s name and email, as well as the popular and featured job listings
* `JobCard.js`: A reusable component that displays a single job listing as a card

## Styles

The app uses a custom stylesheet to match the provided UI design. The stylesheet is located in `styles.js`.

## Notes

* This app uses React Native and JavaScript to build the user interface and logic.
* The app does not persist user data or job listings; this is a simple demo app.
* You can customize the app by modifying the components, styles, and data.

